This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with visual understanding of complex urban street scenes and object detection using deep learning. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories as deep learning is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Additionally, it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category as the dataset can be used for autonomous driving and robotics applications. Finally, it may belong to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) category as the paper deals with semantic labeling of urban scenes.
